"n.礼仪；使人感到舒适的事物 【英】 n. 带来愉快的设施; 适意(a desirable feature; convenience) 【考】 amenity: comfortable / honorarium : grateful(适意表示舒服/酬金 表示感谢) 【记】 和amenable一起记， 都是以amen开头 【例】 The hotel's amenities included a whirlpool. n. 带来愉快的设施(使人身体或物质上感到舒适的事物); 适意(使人愉快或吸引人的性质) = amiability = cordiality = geniality 【例】Stadiums and gymnasia are just some of the town'apos;s local amenities 运动场和体育馆只是镇上的部份康乐设施. 【根】amoenus令人愉快的 【记】a一个, men男人, ity名词后缀. 一个男人. 一个男人从某种程度上讲, 更是带来愉快的""quot;设施""quot;. 【类】amenity: comfortable = honorarium: grateful适意表示舒服 = 酬金表示感谢 【记】音：阿门，常对上帝说阿门能带来精神上的愉快，去教堂时穿着也有礼仪 amenity (n.)  late 14c., ""quality of being pleasant or agreeable,"" from Old French amenite, from Latin amoenitatem (nominative amoenitas) ""delightfulness, pleasantness,"" from amoenus ""pleasant,"" perhaps related to amare ""to love"" (see Amy)."
